    {
      "title": "Notebook Header",
      "text": "%md\n\n# Comprehensive EDA — Arabic AI-Text Detection\n\n## MSBDA-801 Big Data Analytics — Phase 1.4 + 2.3\n\nThis Zeppelin notebook generates the complete EDA visualizations required by **Task 1.4** (initial data exploration: structure, types, label distribution) and **Task 2.3** (word clouds, n-gram frequency, vocabulary richness — TTR) using **Spark DataFrames** on the Apache Zeppelin environment.\n\n### Outputs\n1. Data structure (`printSchema` + types + label distribution)\n2. Type-Token Ratio (TTR) Human vs AI\n3. Word cloud Human vs AI\n4. Top-20 words Human vs AI\n5. Top-20 bigrams (n-grams) Human vs AI\n6. AI-distinctive bigrams (AI fingerprints)\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Spark 3.x runtime\n- HDFS Parquet input at `hdfs://localhost:9000/user/$USER/arabic_nlp/data/processed`\n- Python libs: matplotlib, seaborn, wordcloud, arabic-reshaper, python-bidi",
